eran_foundation-1-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/ed_sheeran_foundation-1-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/ed_sheeran_foundation-1-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3848495" class="wp-caption-text"> Ed Sheeran at Rockefeller Plaza on June 06, 2023 in New York City. (Photo by Dia Dipasupil/Getty Images)</figcaption></figure><p> He explained to Fallon: “I was in that lawsuit a couple of years ago and in the lawsuit, they order you to give up all your old devices. So I handed everything in, but I moved to a tablet in 2015 just on e-mail. I switched my phone off 2015 and left it in a box. And then, when I went through that lawsuit, I got my phone out again and had to go through like all the voice notes and the pictures and all that stuff for the lawyers.”</p><p> He went on to describe the experience as “going into a time machine.” When he went through the phone, he came across text messages from two friends who had since died, an argument with an ex-girlfriend, and correspondence with an estranged family member he hadn&#39;t spoken to in a decade: “It really, really spun me out.”</p><p> Check out the performance below. </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="埃德·希兰（Ed Sheeran" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/awbaFPhoACA?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> Speaking on &#39;Play&#39; – which has yet to receive a release date – Sheeran said that his next string of albums will be influenced by controls on record plays. Where his previous collection of albums was inspired by mathematical symbols (&#39;Plus&#39;, &#39;Multiply&#39;, &#39;Divide&#39;, &#39;Subtract&#39; and &#39;Equals&#39;), his next collection should include titles like &#39;Pause&#39;, &#39;Fast Forward&#39;, &#39;Rewind&#39; and &#39;Stop&#39;.</p><p> He also suggested that he&#39;s already planning for a posthumous release, that will contain songs written through several decades of his life and will be released upon his death. He joked that the album could be called &#39;Eject&#39;. He <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/ed-sheeran-is-already-planning-for-a-posthumous-album-3418059">first hinted at the posthumous album in 2023 and said that it&#39;s a “continuous work”</a> .</p><p> Earlier this month, Sheeran confirmed that <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/ed-sheeran-confirms-that-his-new-album-is-done-and-teases-single-3847662">work on &#39;Play&#39; is “done” and that an official single will be arriving “soon”</a> . The update follows <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/watch-ed-sheeran-debut-new-song-during-surprise-new-orleans-street-performance-3846796">a surprise set on the streets of New Orleans, where he was joined by a brass band and initially debuted the new song</a> . </p><figure id="attachment_3821449" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3821449" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3821449" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/EdSheeran-already-finished-new-album.jpg" alt="Ed Sheeran performing live on stage" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/EdSheeran-already-finished-new-album.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/EdSheeran-already-finished-new-album-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/EdSheeran-already-finished-new-album-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/EdSheeran-already-finished-new-album-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/EdSheeran-already-finished-new-album-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/EdSheeran-already-finished-new-album-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3821449" class="wp-caption-text"> Ed Sheeran performing live. CREDIT: Theo Wargo/Getty</figcaption></figure><p> Meanwhile, the singer previously revealed that <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/ed-sheeran-confirms-new-single-is-coming-next-month-reveals-upcoming-song-titles-3845335">a new song called &#39;Sapphire&#39; would be released in the coming months</a> . He took to social media to <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/EdSheeran/comments/1j4gn8m/azizam_321/?share_id=IV1m1Y5KzxmQKscGWgp7K&amp;utm_content=1&amp;utm_medium=ios_app&amp;utm_name=ioscss&amp;utm_source=share&amp;utm_term=1" target="_blank" rel="noopener">respond to a fan</a> who asked which song of his he should play at his wedding, saying: “Depends when you&#39;re getting married, coz there&#39;s a fair few new options coming soon”.</p><p> The hints about new music come as Sheeran ended 2024 by <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/ed-sheeran-reveals-hes-already-finished-his-new-album-3821440">revealing that he had already finished his next record</a> . “It feels like I&#39;m getting back into big pop for the first time in a long time,” he explained of the LP&#39;s sound.</p><p> This came after <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/ed-sheeran-is-working-on-new-music-but-it-wont-come-out-this-year-3753495">Sheeran said last May that he had made some new material</a> , but was waiting a little longer to share it. He told fans: “I released two records on tour last year and it&#39;s quite a lot being on tour and releasing records. So, I&#39;ve made the new music and I&#39;m just going to sit on it for a bit.”</p><p> The forthcoming album will mark his first since 2023&#39;s <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/ed-sheeran-autumn-variations-review-lyrics-tracklist-3505933">&#39;Autumn Variations&#39;</a> , which marked the follow-up to the hit release <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/ed-sheeran-review-subtract-lyrics-3439379">&#39;-&#39; (&#39;Subtract&#39;)</a> . The latter was said to be the final entry into Sheeran&#39;s long-running mathematical-themed series.</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/watch-ed-sheeran-debut-nostalgic-new-song-old-phone-on-fallon-3849953">Watch Ed Sheeran debut nostalgic new song &#39;Old Phone&#39; on &#39;Fallon&#39;</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
